summary: And there’s something to be proud of about moving on and realizing that real love shines golden like starlight, and doesn’t fade...
body: And there’s something to be proud of about moving on and realizing that real love shines golden like starlight, and doesn’t fade or spontaneously combust. Maybe I’ll write a whole album about that kind of love if I ever find it. But this album is about the other kinds of love that I’ve recently fallen in and out of. Love that was treacherous, sad, beautiful, and tragic. But most of all, this record is about love that was red.

summary: I’m not active on tumblr much only on Instagram & twitter but I had to take the time to reminisce, 6 years of RED. I always...
body:
I’m not active on tumblr much only on Instagram & twitter but I had to take the time to reminisce, 6 years of RED. I always thank @taylorswift because each album represents where I was in my life & what Taylor helped me over come good or bad. It’s always a chance to reflect on how far Tay came but myself as well. RED. First of all I was 18 I made my mom go get the CD because I didn’t have my license yet I was still in driving lessons. I remember anxiously waiting for her to come with it and I remember sitting on my floor listening to the whole album over and over until knew the lyrics to every song. I remember wanting tickets SO bad because I have never been to a concert of hers at this point because I live in Newfoundland & we have to fly to Toronto to see her so we couldn’t afford it. I remember saving money & the tickets being sold out. I was devastated. Then Christmas came & my dad surprised me the tickets and I remember only seeing Taylor Swift on the tickets and I bawled my eyes out. I’ve been going to concerts ever since. Taylor have always been like an old friend because we go way back to the first time she started & she have always been there for me when nobody else was even though we didn’t meet she still got me through so many things so this was a huge deal. It was my graduating year so I remember finishing my biology exam going to the airport right after the concert the next day having to drive with my cousin and nan back across Canada to Newfoundland and made it just in time for graduation like the evening before. This era brought me so many memories & im so happy myself & Taylor grew from that person. Thank you Taylor for writing RED & I’m so proud of you! Xoxoxo @taylornation

summary: Red is such an interesting color to correlate with emotion, because it’s on both ends of the spectrum. On one end you have...
body: Red is such an interesting color to correlate with emotion, because it’s on both ends of the spectrum. On one end you have happiness, falling in love, infatuation with someone, passion, all that. On the other end, you’ve got obsession, jealousy, danger, fear, anger and frustration. All those emotions — spanning from intense love, intense frustration, jealousy, confusion, all of that — in my mind, all those emotions are red. You know, there’s nothing in between. There’s nothing beige about any of those feelings, it all comes back to me, and it’s red.
